rComments: I wouldnt recommend taking a course with her because her grading is really really tough. It definitely didnt feel like a 2nd year course. I can understand her grading if it were a 3rd/4th year course, but for a 2nd year course it was a little excessive. All her slides are dr Leveys which makes me think she was thrown into the course last minute.

Shes a super hard marker and kind of expects a lot for just a second year course, but shes also not the worst Ive ever had. She comes off as the type of PhD student who thinks theyre way above their students rather than wanting their students to succeed. She does try hard to get students engaged though, lol it just doesnt work.

Yasmine is a PhD student who expects a stupid amount from second year students. Her grading is harsh, unfair, and unrealistic. Her teaching style is additionally quite dry and her expectations for students are unclear. Her course is not difficult but her grading is.
